==English==

{{rank|return|call|speak|355|land|why|women|cried}}

===Etymology===
From Middle English < Old English '''land''', '''lond''' (ground, soil, defined piece of land, country) < Proto-Germanic '''[[*landom]]''' < Proto-Indo-European '''[[*lendh-]]''' (land, heath).

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|/lănd/}}
*{{IPA|/lænd/}}
*{{SAMPA|/l{nd/}}
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ænd|Rhymes: -ænd]]

===Noun===
'''land''' (''plural:'' '''[[lands]]''')

# The part of [[Earth]] which is not covered [[ocean]]s or other bodies of water.
# Real estate or [[landed]] [[property]]; a partitioned and measurable area which is owned and on which [[buildings]] can be [[erected]].
# A [[country]] or [[region]].
# Ground that is suitable for [[farming]].

